aking a subsample of bases from the input data? \n\nI am struggling to replicate the dada2 tutorial analysis https://benjjneb.github.io/dada2/tutorial.html and I have found some differences with the output from R.\n\nIf there is anything I can run or any way I can help to assist with this please do let me know\n\nBest wishes\nOllie","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1627469484,"nonce":"eNIfN+eXU3Dbvf69EhtZg2hITwI=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s408Q4O","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3848#issuecomment-888213006"},"message":"Here is an updated link to a galaxy history https://usegalaxy.eu/u/ollie_white/h/dada2-learnerrors\n\nThe history has the filtered reads as generated in R. The learn error step has been run for the forward reads and should read \"33514080 total bases in 139642 reads from 20 samples will be used for learning the error rates.\"\n\nCheers\nOllie","files":null}]}